Wanted to thank the Epicurious community for some fantastic recommendations. This was absolutely the best I've ever had and will be repeated next year if not before. Here's the variation on the theme I used: 2.75 lb. brisket placed in cast-iron enameled pot with 4-5 small onions halved/skins on; 2 celery stalks with leaves, 3-4 fresh thyme sprigs. I filled the pot with water up to about 1/2 the height of the brisket. I let it go in a 285 degree oven for about 3 hours. Added potatoes and carrots to the pot and cooked for 1 hour longer. Removed potatoes and carrots and brisket from pot. Quartered cabbage and added to pot and brought to a boil on stove top/covered so I could use broiler. Cabbage took about 15 minutes to cook. Fantastic flavor since is was cooking with all the juices from the brisket/potatoes/carrots. Added spicy mustard and brown sugar to the top of brisket and broiled to form a nice crust. It took about 3-4 minutes once the broiler was hot. WOW! Fantastic!!

