I used this method in the past and decided that cooking the veggies with the beef may have added flavour but ended up becoming sodden and shapeless. I now braise the corned beef with beer and pickling spice alone. I boil the veggies(carrots, small white onions, baby red potatoes) in separate batches in water on top of the stove until al dente while the meat is cooking. I strain the veggies with a slotted spoon and add coarsely chopped cabbage to the boiling water just long enough to have it wilt. I melt 1/2 stick of butter and add lots of dill weed, then pour it over the cooked veggies. The taste is fresher and the dill is a wonderful contrast. I think I will try broiling the corned beef technique at the end with the sugar and mustard as a change..

