I actually do not like my corned beef boiled. Around my house, I cook the corned beef just like I would an oven roast. I put the corned beef in my covered roaster, add water until it comes half-way up the roast, and cook at 300* for 2 hours. Then I add the carrot chunks, waxy potatoes, and of course, 2 quartered cabbages (my son complains if I only cook 1- he loves it this way) I then bake it for about another hour and a half or so- until the potatoes are done. It is great this way- the meat has tons of flavor, and is not mushy or tough at all. The vegis have lots of flavor as well, since they were not boiled to death.

