Good recipe, but have to agree with others, the pressure cooker is definitely the way to go with corned beef. Shorter cooking time, much better flavor. Any size pressure cooker that will hold all the ingredients should be fine. I use a huge old canning pressure cooker that belonged to my grandmother. Note: If you decide to try pressure cooking a corned beef, I suggest you use the phased method. Cook the roast alone with liquid (I like to add a teaspoon of cumin, yum!) for about 40 minutes, then add the veggies, get back up to pressure and cook for 10 more minutes. Your veggies otherwise will be mush. Make plenty, the leftovers are heavenly, too!

