Rating: 4
Delicious as written but can be improved upon. A group of friends enjoy corned beef & cabbage about 4-5 times a year and we decided to conduct an experiment. A blind taste test. We baked, boiled (as with this recipe) and pressure cooked (steamed) 3 identical briskets. The unanimous (8/8) winner was the pressure cooked version with vegetables cooked separately. Better texture and better flavor in the meat and the veggies weren't "greasy". The big plus was the pressure cooker reduced the cooking time to roughly 2 hrs. total.

Rating: 2
If you own a pressure cooker - use it. If not, go and buy one. It makes a huge difference when making corned beef. Cook it 2 hours or so, with carrots, onions, (turnips, parsnips if you like) then add cabbage for last 15 minutes.

Rating: 4
This is a fabulous recipe, far better, more flavorful and easier than the "modern" method of cooking the veggies at the last minute to keep "crisp." Here the flavors blend beautifully and the dish sings out with flavor. Don't forget the dry mustard, or to have some reconstituted along with the beef itself.